caption: Awesome atmosphere!
Nice but a bit expensive.
There brussels sprouts were very good. They were honey glazed with bacon. An very very good tasting. I will definitely go back just because of brussel sprouts. 😊

The bar was really nice. All the male employees were super friendly and helpful. One female bartender and another waitress were not very friendly. The man who I believe may have been the manager was very nice and accommodating. The food and drinks were DELICIOUS!

Great location..Good ambience..poor service..the servers we had today were inattentive, forgot basic stuff like ketchup for fries, salt and pepper, napkins, refilling water. Needed constant reminders. They had a clumsy, non-server attitude. Mood spoiler. Wasn’t  happy with service..olive garden provides with better service.. food was kind of okay..overall a very average  experience..

The Good: Server Raul was cheerful, upbeat and attentive. The Bad: Food and drinks were underwhelming: the crab dip and oysters Rockefeller we're composed of a similar uninspiring goop, and the cocktails were, stingy. The Ugly: specifically requested in advance a table away from the kitchen by a window (note: there were plenty of other tables before we were seated, so shame on me for not pointing this out on the spot). We were eventually seated at a small table in front of a service closet which contained food takeout materials and other supplies. The staff needed to access this supply closet three times in the first 10 minutes of us being seated. Accessing the closet required us to stand up and move our chairs and table ~ Giving the staff a helping hand on occasion is always appropriate. However, it was obvious that the staff was annoyed with this table's location, and was becoming increasingly annoyed with us for not moving our chairs and table fast enough. After approaching the maitre'd, explaining that this situation would be untenable for a sit-down meal, he (without a word), gestured to a new table that was a good fit. Bottom line: If you're headed to Loch Bar for the location you're going to the right spot ~ as for cuisine and hospitality, you'll need to manage your expectations.
Was ok. Very casual. Not what I expected from Atlas...

The food was DELICIOUS! I have a new restaurant to add to my favorites list! The crab grilled cheese was so good. The Frosé was a bar favorite. My boyfriend had the crab shrimp and fried oyster club sandwich. It was HUGE! I will definitely return to this place!
I have now visited this place 3 times and it’s safe to say I just do not like the food. It’s very meh. Presentation is very good, however the flavor just isn’t there. Service is always excellent tho!

This place has always been one of my favorite spots in Baltimore.  The raw bar is always on point, as is the whiskey selection.  The fact that they usually have stone crab claws (when in season) is an added bonus.  Unfortunately, my most recent experience has probably hindered any future visits.  After driving all day from North Carolina, I entered the restaurant on Saturday, March 6th at around 3pm.  Assuming that we would be able to quickly get a table or bar stools, I went up to the person tending the host stand.  This is where the trip took a turn for the worse.  The man, wearing a dark suit with glasses, middle-aged, informed me that he had absolutely nothing available.  He did not offer to put me on a list, he simply turned me away, looking down his nose at me the entire time.  The place was very busy, unexpectedly.  I understand this can happen.  But, this man made no attempt to possibly accommodate us, even at a future time.  We were completely turned away.  I should also point out, we were dressed more than properly for the location.  My wife and I used to stay at the Four Seasons whenever we came to Fells Point / Inner harbor (3-4 times per year).  We have been staying at the Sagamore Pendry mostly now, but always make our way over to Loch Bar because we loved it so much.  We will not be coming here again, which is disappointing, considering the thousands of dollars I’ve thrown through this place.  Thames Street Oyster Bar, right in the heart of Fells Point, and across the street from the Sagamore Pendry, will be our new Raw Bar destination in Baltimore.
The crab was great but the incredible thing was the scallop ceviche. Worth every penny

I have mixed feelings writing this review.  My friend and i went here for the first time.  We decided to split our main courses so we can taste more of their menu.  We ordered the crab cakes and the seabass.  The crab cakes were delicious. Lots of chunks of crab meat. The seabass however.... was SUPER SALTY. And me and my friend decided for a while whether we should complain and ask for a new one. And we decided yes. It's an expensive restaurant so we felt like we deserved to have it replaced with how much we paid for the food. The oysters were good as well and our cosmopolitan drinks.  When she told the our server that it was so salty, she was just staring at us.. Like awkward silence. No apology.... No "do you want me to take it back and get you a new one?".. nothing. So my friend finally broke the silence and said if we could have it switched.  I think our server was annoyed because we took so long to go over the menu and order because my friend and i were talking so much. But hey, it was our first time hanging out outside of work so we had a lot to talk about. We weren't rude though. We didnt do it on purpose. And we kept apologizing to her because we took a long time.  Server said yes and we got a new one and it was still SUPER SALTY. 😞 PLEASE if you have hypertension or heart failure,  do not order this!! I guess that's just how it is. We ended up not eating much of it.  Our experience got better because their Manager was very nice and talked to us.  I mean, the place is very beautiful. But it's an expensive restaurant and I expected more for our server. Ive been to Bygone which is owned by the same group and their customer service was top notch!

A bit pricey but definitely worth it for the views and vibe. Food is good overall, but reason for 4 stars is the Oyster shucking quality varies from time to time. At close to $4 a piece, we expect it to be clean and shucked without any pieces of shell falling into the Oyster meat at all. Last 5 or so visits 2 times we had to spit out little pieces of shell when slurping the oysters. Encourage staff to take the time to shuck with care even when busy. No one likes crunchy oysters.
Ask for Ian at the bar. He’s tall and bald with a bow tie. Delicious drinks and great service ‼️ Jacki the next day was amazing. We even got the hoof‼️
Nice view and cute atmosphere....enjoyed the croissant sandwich........it wasn't slap your mama great but was not overall bad....😊😊😊
Wonderfuls cocktails, delicious food and attentive staff. Will come back in the future!

Selected the Loch Bar for my 31st birthday dinner. Our party size of 11 was accommodated in advance. The décor was pleasant and kinda chic  but the atmosphere is overall dry so I wouldn't return for a celebration. My server never once told me happy birthday even when she carded me and of course no type of sweet treat was offered but life goes on.  Drink service was fairly prompt but no personality given from the staff (I'm from the industry as well so its always nice to feel a connection with your server)  Food service was interesting in terms of delivery (trickled out as the dishes were ready) Oddly the manager came over, not to wish me a happy birthday but to tell us the Loch Bar doesn't allow balloons? That would have been good information to have shared while I was booking the reservation so we were forced to hide them underneath our table- again just odd lol just an interesting birthday dinner and one not to be repeated at The Loch Bar- just not a fun vibe.

Disgusted! We had a reservation for 9:15pm on Saturday, however arrived early (8:45pm). Where do I start? Unfortunately we didn’t get to enjoy our time there because the restaurant took an hour bringing our entree’s out. Another reservation (of another race) was seated AFTER us and received their drinks and entree’s before us. My husband spoke to the manager, and he offered us “Free” drinks, stating “We didn’t expect to be this busy”— I expressed that I wasn’t interested in drinks and somehow the waitress STILL brings us drinks (which we declined again). It was going on 10:00pm with no plate in sight. By 10:15pm our food arrives and to say the least we were very unimpressed. Our waitress showed no sign of compassion or sympathy. In result, we boxed our food and desert. Honestly, I would’ve left if it wasn’t for my husband taking initiative for Valentine’s Day date night. Ultimately, we felt disregarded by this restaurant and staff. Also, after doing research and speaking with peers this seems to be an ongoing experience for Black people. Tasteless and not worth it! Go upstairs and enjoy yourself at Bygone.
Pretty decent. Overpriced ($8 for a bottle of water?!) But I guess it's not unexpected for the location and type of restaurant. Overall, not a bad experience. Would go again.
My favorite spot in town love it 🤗

seafood... very delicious. i love this place, great food & service. the service was very helpful and welcoming. the bill was fair for the quality of the food. food is like a restaurant in louisville i loved.

My boyfriend and I came over the summer. The charcuterie board Taste good and the presentation was excellent. The drinks were not to bad as well, I had a spiked Arnold Palmer and a neat bourbon. The crab soup was 8/10 would order again
Very neat and accessible spot. They provide big portions and for inexpensive rates. I enjoyed the food very much and the staff members were super affable and chatty. I recommend this place.
The location of the bar was perfect. We can easily go to this place whenever we want. The theme of this place was very professional. We spent a good time here with my colleagues. Great!

The food was fantastic and the drinks were spectacular! I loved every moment of it, the waiter was so kind and so accommodating! This was my first time here and it won’t be my last! A must visit.

The most unprofessional, unfriendly and  abrasive service I've ever received from a restaurant of the caliber. I have never felt so unwelcome. I would recommend going upstairs to Bygone or next door to Azumi. I would never recommend surrendering your money to such vultures.
The manager was so sweet and helpful. The food was also good,  when it actually came out. The service left a lot to be desired, however the view was spectacular,  and the drinks were good.  Solid 3/5

Loved this restaurant. Great food. The maî·tre d' immediately sat us. We got our choice of area to sit in. The restaurant looked to be adhering to all Covid-19 CDC recommendations. The bench seats are plush and comfortable. The ambiance was on point. The music was enjoyable and but to loud. Menu was limited, as most are because of Covid but it was plentiful enough with different choices to choose from. There was lots of parking on the streets (under five blocks walking) and there are plenty of garages in the area, one being right next door. Great choice for date night or just going out with a group of friends. A good spot to eat and I would definitely come back if I'm in the area.
Great atmosphere awesome food and service..a must try if you are in Baltimore
Small portion sizes, food over priced, nice decor tho...

Amazing food with a great view!  I am always skeptical of places right on the water of being overpriced and mediocre but this place is worth it!  The adult grilled cheese complete with gouda, bacon and loaded with CRAB is delicious.  The drinks are tasty!  I couldn't decide between the two crab soups so they did 1/2 and 1/2 and it was good.  I love my mussels and fries and the brussel sprouts were cooked to perfection and have a bit of sweet and spicy to them.  We had amazing service and look forward to going back!

Our first time was AMAZING!! Ian was wonderful... we'll be back

If you're looking for a great restaurant for a night out with your girls or to celebrate with your lover in downtown Baltimore, this is the place! The food and cocktails were absolutely delicious! Everything we ordered, from the crab dip to the steamed shrimps, to the oysters, scallops, crab cakes and filet mignon was well seasoned and tasty. The ambiance of the restaurant overlooking the baltimore harbor was great. You have the option of seating outdoors or dinning indoors. You also get great view of the water if you sit in one of the booths indoors. On Saturday night, they have a band playing music which adds to the overall vibe of the restaurant. The staff was pleasant. Our server, Raoul was very patient with us. He offered suggestions even without prompting and he was on point with his suggestions. In terms of pricing, the price is a little on the higher end. One of the cocktails (Sidecar with Hennessy) was about $26 which is on very steep. It is unclear if their pricing have to do with COVID because a lot of restaurants do charge an extra fee due to COVID restrictions and additional measures they have to take. Nonetheless, I highly recommend this restaurant and will definitely be returning in the near future.
I tried every oyster, they were all uniquely delicious. We sat outside next to the water. Our server was friendly and accommodating.

Salmon and shrimp salad was very good. The shrimp and salmon were grilled and had such a bold taste of herbs. Didn't really need  any dressing on it being that the herbs complimented the taste.  The scenery is beautiful as well.
Ok spot for Seafood. I can say this place does it for me. I think I might become a regular. The bill was good for how much you get. Food and feeling reminds me of Kansas City.

One star has been earned by the amazing bussers( they were on top of the game) and one star is given to the server that was not even assigned to us(a young gentleman took care of us while our server was unable to)...I normally am very understanding if the place is busy, but it was not. The food was fresh, but they unfortunately forgot the lemons when they brought out one of the towers of raw seafood. If the waitress stopped by to check up on us it could have been easily fixed and unnoticeable....But she didn’t... The manager also seemed like she was just waiting to close and go home....Nobody really seemed to care...I strongly believe that for the type of level of dining that this place positions itself it should have a better service. At least a little more attentive... P.S. Scallop entree was indeed delicious.
Terrific location, very good food, excellent server; John.
Great view, fabulous food and presentation, and attentive service. Good for a romantic date or meeting a friend.

Love this place. Ambience is sexy, water views, romantic, great for a date night. Awesome drinks, french fries are amazing, delicious oysters. This place is a guaranteed winner every time in Baltimore. Everything on menu is good. The service is always on point here also.

✨Very Beautiful Experience! Great vibes, Great Drinks, Service was Perfect 👌, the food is Great!!! The valet parking was a little slow in the beginning BUT it was packed. I am happy they have valet parking, I didn't want to walk too far in heels. I would sooo go again. New Fave Spot!✨

I’m glad they open for lunch. It was a gorgeous day to sit outside and have a few drinks and some food. The slushes, which do contain alcohol, come in two varieties: Frosé and Bourbon. I had the Frosé- it was fantastic! The menu is so extensive; I had a hard time choosing. I love the variety of food and drink options. It’s a bit pricey, but what do you expect being attached to the Four Seasons Hotel?

So my mother & I came  to this restaurant for the very time this past Sunday. From the pictures it looks more upscale by in reality it’s very dis organized. Our reservation was initially set for us to eat outside but the noise level drove us to go inside. So we sat at our second seating which was in a dingy corner right next to the door that had flies around us. Once again we asked to be seated somewhere else before we made the decision to leave. We sat at a more suitable area & by this time my mom and I were annoyed. It wasn’t just us because the entire evening people were requesting to change their seating because the disorganization is prevalent there.  The bathroom was filthy, the floors were dirty & it smelled like feces, I didn’t go to the bathroom, I just held it in.  The food was subpar. The steak that I wanted they didn’t have anymore so I only ordered a drink. My mom ordered Chilean sea bass & it was probably a 6/10. The fries were very salty. The only thing good was the Brussel sprouts. On her meal she spent close to $90. And in all honesty it wasn’t worth it.  Our waiter was very friendly & I would give him a 5 star ⭐️ if i could.  Unfortunately we won’t be coming back.

Loch Bar is an upscale seafood restaurant in the Four Seasons Hotel near Baltimore’s Inner Harbor. It includes a large raw bar that includes clams, mussels, oysters, crab, and shrimp. The food is very good, but on the expensive side. The restaurant is also known for its very lengthy whisky list. Loch bar is nicely decorated and outside patio dining is also available. Our Server, Kyle, was very friendly and helpful. Also, there is live music seven nights a week.

Loch Bar is one of my favorite restaurants in the city! They pretty much have it all... location, amptoshpere and the food! My go-to meal is the lobster roll, amazing fries, and an oragne crush! As soon as social distancing is over this is the first place we are eating!

Loch bar was a very nice restaurant. They have a wide assortment of fresh oysters on display at the bar. They have a vast selection of bourbon and whiskey. The apps we tried were ok, but not great (fried pickles were sub-par... Tasted like they're made with bread and butter pickles). The drink "Loch Bar" IIRC was fantastic! The bartender, taller bald/bearded white guy was attentive, friendly, and helpful when needed. Recommend.

Been here a few times. A Baltimore gem. Pricey, but worth every penny. Between the food, ambiance, service, and live music, you cannot go wrong here. Unrivaled. Stop reading this, and go eat here.

Other than that honestly I wasn't very impressed by the food. I ate there three times during my stay in Baltimore Harbor. The ambiance it decent and restaurant was kind of small but cozy. My family of 10 made a reservation at the Loch Bar expecting delicious food, great scenery, and excellent service.  The food and outdoor area itself were as expected, however, we were incredibly disappointed with our waiter.  He was rude, dismissive, and inattentive.  He also refused to consult the chef regarding a dietary restriction and responded with a request about the menu stating "We can't do anything for you except a salad without cheese."  I highly doubt the chefs at this restaurant couldn't have prepared an entree or sides without dairy.  At times it took 30 minutes to see our waiter again.  This was supposed to be an important meal for our family and I would highly recommend people avoid this restaurant if you're looking for at least an average service experience.

Great location and view, very good crab soup, friends had Cobb salad with ahi tuna that was huge and she said was excellent, 1/2chicken w vegetables was abundant and tastey, wife's filet carrots and twice baked potatoes were delicious, my swordfish was tender and excellent but the scant amount of quinoa was disappointing,  service was decent.

great food, period.  we ordered raw oyster (4 different kinds) fried oyster (so succulent and soft it melts in your mouth), cream of crab soup (super good with hint of spiciness) and french onion soup (properly made just in paris).  for entree, we got Maine diver scallop, rock fish and filet mignon (of course! why would you come to the place like this and not order the best cut of the beef?) all were just simply excellent.  both my husband and i have been to some of the best steak houses in the country and around the world, we were both impressed with the cooking here.  service was attentive and no fuss.  the only thing i think they could have done better was 1) offer some dinner rolls free... really, for the $300 dinner, you can afford to give your guest some dinner breads like all the other good steak houses (capital grille, del fresco) 2) we were there for early dinner, and it is happy hour. half price draft was offered but only if you sit by the bar.  why?! you'd rather cater to people who do not spend as much money? again, not what i have typically experienced in a high end place.  maybe it is just baltimore.  not that i care about $4 which comes about 1% of my total bill. but when you are a pricy place, you need to act more like real posh establishment as opposed to just being pricy.

This is my 3rd trip to loch bar and I must say I really love this place! I am completely obsessed with their frose’. It is perfectly sweet and also leaves you with a slight buzz (which is great because I feel like most frozen drinks lack alcohol even if they say it’s there). On my most recent visit I tried the crab dip and it was delicious with a decent amount of lump crab meat (being a Marylander I am very critical of dishes that contain crab so I approve of this dish! Lol). I ordered the crab grilled cheese with a side salad drizzled with a vinaigrette. I loved it and would definitely order again. The salad was a nice fresh compliment to the heaviness of the sandwich. My aunt who accompanied me ordered the shrimp salad with fries and she enjoyed her food as well. Our visit was to celebrate my aunts birthday so they surprised us with mini shot glass sized versions of their frozen whiskey drink (which was less sweet than the frozen but also a good drink option), an oatmeal chocolate chip skillet cookie topped with a vanilla ice cream bar covered in a dark chocolate shell. I am not a chocolate chip fan but this cookie was very warm and yummy! Needless to say I highly recommend this restaurant and if you don’t try anything else I mentioned please order the frose!  PS they also offer nice outdoor seating which I believe is heated during the colder months.

Had crab dip to start (done perfect Baltimore style), a few oysters (if you like briney, try the Loch or the Raspberry oysters), and finished it with an apple crisp that had the best bourbon carmel. We went after 9pm , so as to avoid a massive crowd, but the atmosphere was incredible with live music and the staff are very attentive and welcoming. Oh....if you likegood bourbon , like I do, check out the menu. It won't disappoint .

I will start by saying that my past experiences with restaurants attached to hotels has been uneven at best - and more than often awful. Exception here. Loch Bar is a NYC-ish designed environment. As for happy hour, what can be pricey at other times is quite reasonable in the immediate after-work hours. Now, on certain evenings this will lead to an influx of people looking for a bargain. And Loch Bar can get noisy. However, the beer list is quite decent, the happy hour wines exceptional (and that is as rare find), the oysters cold, plump and juicy and rest of the menu well-done. And the noise level will subside after the 6PM hour. Multiple servers behind the bar provide cordial and attentive service. If I lived/worked in Harbor East or Fells, this would be my permanent hangout. Preference over Pendry. If it's Happy Hour. Go enjoy. Other times, Loch Bar can be a wee-bit pricey

Food: Good   (Customer)Service: AWFUL. My husband, brother, and I are regulars at Loch bar on Sundays! We love their happy hour from 3-7 and their oysters are to die for. Today (Saturday) we decided we would go to the outside bar since it was sunny out. We usually see Sam, but today there was a guy working. We asked for a couple orange crushes and my brother asked for a draft beer. The bartender initially said it wouldn’t be a problem, but then he switched it up and said going in and out would be “too much work” so my brother could not order a draft beer. REALLY? - we didn’t let that get to us and he ordered a crush as well. From the time we sat down and when we finished our drinks, our bartender went inside at least 6 different times. While we were paying, we actually witnessed the bartender go inside and bring a frozé out to a girl who was sitting next to us. Seriously?.. We asked for our check and decided to go inside to drink the draft beer my brother was craving and also ordered some oysters. Frustrated, I asked to speak to a manager on duty about my experience and he said “thanks for your feedback but the froze is a different machine than the draft beers so we do allow those outside.” WHAT? Lol. That’s the most ridiculous thing I have ever heard. So you would rather inconvenience your PAYING customers and have them go inside if they want a draft beer than have your employee bring it out while he brings the froze out? That’s logical. I will not be returning to this place when they don’t take customer feedback seriously. They could care less to turn a bad experience into something positive, as long as they are making money - and trust me, this place isn’t cheap. I work in customer service myself and the right answer from a GM should’ve been “I apologize for your poor experience, that is not what we strive for and feedback will be provided. How can we make this up to you?” I expected more from The Atlas Group..  very disappointing

We took the whole office there for a birthday lunch. Excellent drinks (especially the Frosé) but the food needs some major help. Sandwiches were fine but the Seafood was insanely salty. Like "someone is playing a joke on you" salty. The topic of conversation in the office the next couple of days was how gassy and bloated we were. We now have a running joke that whomever is late for a meeting has to eat at Loch Bar without access to a bathroom after.
